rows.TITLE: Data tracking not possible: Tracking keys have duplicate entries.
rows.DESCRIPTION: You can check what properties are used as ID by searching your API Schema for the property `x-object-uid`. All properties in that list will be used together as ID. If at least two input rows match in all ID properties, they are seen as duplicates. To fix this issue, deduplicate your data set or request adding additional ID properties if necessary.
rows.HINT: Your input data contained one or more duplicate IDs. Data tracking was disabled, which may result in mismatched logging data.

rows.TITLE: Some rows encountered issues.
DESCRIPTION: This means that one or more of your input rows had some issues. Have a look at the error log and search for the row numbers provided with this message. If you can't find a matching error or can't determine the issue, you can export the affected row numbers with the `Export Row Numbers` button to check your input data directly. Look for common issues, such as spelling mistakes, mislabeled columns and so on.
If you cannot fix the issue yourself, contact support with your input data, the exported row numbers and any additional information that might help with finding a solution.
rows.HINT: The rows listed with this message encountered one or more issues and were rejected. Check the error log for more details.

rows._EXPORT_SUMMARY: 7PNKJ51 Cannot check for duplicates! Not enough data to identify rows.
rows.TITLE: Cannot check for duplicates! Not enough data to identify rows.
DESCRIPTION: This is error occurs when a `FlowStep` attempts to check for duplicates when committing its output data and some of the columns to compare to are missing.

The error message should inform you, where the list of columns to compare to has been defined. Make sure that all attributes in that list are named properly and are present in the input data for this step.
